## Reasoning
The issue described is related to the injection of the `EntityManager` in the `CatalogService` class. In Jakarta EE, the `@PersistenceContext` annotation is used to inject the `EntityManager`. However, in Quarkus, this annotation is not needed if the datasource is correctly configured.

The `@Inject` annotation is used to inject the `EntityManager`, but in Quarkus, this will only work if the `EntityManager` is not produced by a `@Produces` annotation. If a `@Produces` annotation is used, a qualification for the produced `EntityManager` is needed.

In this case, there is no `@Produces` annotation in the provided code, so we can simply remove the `@Stateless` annotation and use the `@Inject` annotation to inject the `EntityManager`.

However, we need to make sure that the `EntityManager` is correctly configured in the Quarkus application. This will typically involve adding the `quarkus-hibernate-orm` dependency to the `pom.xml` file and configuring the datasource in the `application.properties` file.

